Neo-Classicism
Penguin Books | 1977 | ISBN: 0140209786 | English | 228 pages | PDF | 23.8 MB

One of the clearest and verviest volumes of art history. Eye-opening in the best sense: If you think of neoclassicism as a chilly, authoritarian, kaput style and subject, you're in for some surprises. You may even start to find neoclassicism entrancing and exciting. And what a writer. Hugh Honour has an easy, unstressed verbal grace, and an educated and incisive mind
